refs-fuse for Debian
--------------------

Assuming your ReFS partition is /dev/sdb1 and its mountpoint should be /media/refs:

1. Mount an ReFS partition:

     mount -t refs /dev/sdb1 /media/refs

2. To mount the patition at startup, edit /etc/fstab and add:

     /dev/sdb1  /media/refs  refs  defaults  0 0

